    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/621a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Brown Brothers &amp; Company and Seligman &amp;
                            Company</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen</hi>: The Nicaraguan Minister has represented to
                    the Department that the economic conditions now existing in his country render
                    it desirable that the Nicaraguan Government increase its <pb facs="1061" n="945"
                        xml:id="pg_945"/> present loan by $250,000, or perhaps as much as $500,000.
                    The Department will be glad to assist in forwarding any practical measure
                    calculated to relieve the financial conditions now obtaining in Nicaragua.
                    Should you care at this time to consider an increase in your loan to the
                    Government of Nicaragua, the Department will be glad to discuss the matter with
                    your representatives at such time as may best suit your convenience.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
